    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n\r\nWrite a program where the Painter paints horizontal stripes. \r\n1. Add code to finish the `move_and_paint(color)` function definition that will have the Painter paint a continuous line.\r\n2. Call the necessary functions and Painter methods to create the striped pattern.\r\n   - **Hint:** Ensure the Painter moves correctly between rows by adding appropriate turns and movements after each stripe.\r\n\r\n**Bonus Challenge:** Can you make the program more efficient by putting repeated function calls and Painter methods in new user-defined functions?\r\n   \r\n<details style=\"background-color: #e0d1ec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;\">\r\n    <summary style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold; color: black;\">Need help with your algorithm?</summary>\r\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\">\r\n    \t<p style=\"color: black;\">Here is one approach to solving this problem.</p>\r\n        <pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\nwhile the Painter has paint\r\n  if the Painter can move \r\n    paint\r\n    move\r\n\t  </pre>\r\n    </div>\r\n</details>\r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\n# Create Painter object\nkai = Painter()\n\n# Function to turn right\ndef turn_right():\n    kai.turn_left()\n    kai.turn_left()\n    kai.turn_left()\n\n# Function to move forward while possible\ndef move_while_can():\n    while kai.can_move():\n        kai.move()\n\n# Function to take all the paint\ndef take_all_paint():\n  while kai.is_on_bucket():\n    kai.take_paint()\n\n# Function to move and paint while can move\ndef move_and_paint_path(color):\n    # ADD CODE HERE\n        \n\n# ADD FUNCTION CALLS TO COMPLETE THE STRIPE PATTERN\ntake_all_paint()\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
